0: BUKOBA, Tanzania, Sept. 10 (UPI) -- Officials said 11 people were killed and 192 injured after a 5.7-magnitude earthquake struck in northern Tanzania on Saturday. NEWLINE_CHAR NEWLINE_CHAR The quake struck near the western shore of Lake Victoria outside in the city of Bukoba, population 70,000, where a majority of the casualties were reported. Photos posted on social media in Bukoba showed buildings collapsed.
